          <li><strong>Highlights:</strong> Canada's smallest province, tight-knit community, beautiful beaches</li>
          <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Maritime, moderate winters, warm summers</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Newfoundland and Labrador</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Capital:</strong> St. John's (population ~215,000)</li>
          <li><strong>Economy:</strong> Oil & gas (offshore), fishing, mining, tourism</li>
          <li><strong>Highlights:</strong> Unique culture, dramatic landscapes, friendly people</li>
          <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Varied—coastal areas milder, interior can be harsh</li>
        </ul>

